    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-28T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-28T02:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">7510.92/216: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-28T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >January 28, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. An agreement between Thailand and Indochina to cease hostilities became
                    effective at 10 o’clock this morning and armistice negotiations are scheduled to
                    begin here tomorrow.<note n="62" xml:id="d42fn1">In his telegram No. 11,
                        February 1, 11 a.m., Consul Flood reported to the Department the signing of
                        the Thai-Indoehinese armistice on January 31 at 6 p.m. (751G92/227).</note>
                    The Thai delegation is expected from Bangkok by Japanese plane this afternoon
                    and General Sumita<note n="63" xml:id="d42fn2">Maj. Gen. Raishiro Sumita, Chief
                        of the Japanese Military Mission to French Indochina and Chairman of the
                        Truce Conference at Saigon.</note> is arriving by plane from Hanoi. A
                    Japanese cruiser and a smaller vessel of the several Japanese warships observed
                    off Cap Saint Jacques during the past 3 days are also expected at Saigon this
                    afternoon.</p>
                <p>Sent to Cavite for repetition to the Department; Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong,
                    Shanghai. Hong Kong please repeat to Tokyo. Repeated to Bangkok.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Flood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
